comments.body:
@baude @rhatdan Thanks for the quick reply on this one. I might be able to open a PR with a in deep explanation at Saturday (07/18).

I will try to reserve time to work on compatibility. But would say that: Docker and Podman are two different products. So compatibility would be great but not much of a deal breaker. Correct? To be honest I was more concerned with [python-podman](https://github.com/containers/python-podman) at first, rather then docker itself because my intention is to have a library to work on a compose solution for podman itself.

Yes. I aware of the [podman-compose](https://github.com/containers/podman-compose) but this one is not even use any of the libraries AFAIK. The plan is to create a stable library here in starting work with it at either the podman-compose or create my own.
